Headlines.Author: Nathan Becker
Headlines.Headline: Integrys Energy to Sell Upper Peninsula Power to BBIP for $298.8 Million

PARAGRAPH.#text: Integrys Energy Group Inc. said it will sell its Upper Peninsula Power Company business to Balfour Beatty Infrastructure Partners LP for $298.8 million. Integrys, which runs natural-gas and utility operations in the Midwest, said it will record an after-tax gain of 60 cents a share because of the deal. After a one- or two-year transition period, the company said it expects the deal to add about 6 cents to earnings on an ongoing basis. The two companies had been discussing a deal for nearly a year.

Headlines.Author: Kristin Jones
Headlines.Headline: Alliant Energy To Sell Minnesota Businesses for $128 Million

PARAGRAPH.#text: Alliant Energy Corp. LNT has agreed to sell its Minnesota electric and natural gas distribution businesses for a total of $128 million. The electric business will be sold to Southern Minnesota Energy Cooperative, a group of 12 neighboring electric cooperatives, while a unit of Integrys Energy Group Inc. TEG will buy the natural gas business. "Our Minnesota customers will be part of utilities with a significant, long-standing presence in the state," said Tom Aller, president of Alliant Energy's Minnesota and Iowa utility.

Headlines.Author: Mark Peters
Headlines.Headline: POWER POINTS: More Consumers Shop For Power Amid Low Prices

PARAGRAPH.#text: NEW YORK (Dow Jones)--Consumers looking to take advantage of a sharp drop in U.S. power prices are increasingly turning to new suppliers. The majority of customers in deregulated states such as Connecticut, Maryland and Ohio get their power through their local utility, at default rates that don't reflect current wholesale market conditions. However, the economic downturn and boom in natural gas output has driven wholesale prices sharply lower over the past year, driving a growing number of recession-strapped consumers to shop for a new supplier offering cheaper rates.

Headlines.Headline: Integrys' Upper Peninsula Power Unit Denies Fraud Allegations

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Integrys Energy Group Inc.'s

Upper Peninsula Power Co. unit denied NaterraLand allegations that the company committed fraud and misrepresented itself in a land sale contract between the two parties. Upper Peninsula said it hasn't done anything that prevents NaterraLand from developing a major portion of the land they purchased. In late 2005, NaterraLand purchased property adjacent to Upper Peninsula's hydroelectric properties in Michigan Upper Peninsula.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys' Upper Peninsula Power Unit Denies Fraud Allegations

Headlines.Author: Adam O. Manzor
Headlines.Headline: Integrys Engy Grp 4Q EPS $1.11 Vs EPS 49c

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Integrys Energy Group Inc.'s

fourth-quarter net income rose to $85.1 million, or $1.11 a share, from $21.3 million, or 49 cents a share, in the prior-year period. The Chicago-based holding company said revenue jumped 64% to $3.06 billion from $1.86 billion a year ago. Analysts polled by Thomson Financial expected, on average, per-share earnings excluding items of $1.07.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys Engy Grp 4Q EPS $1.11 Vs EPS 49c

Headlines.Author: Monica M. Clark
Headlines.Headline: Integrys Energy Gets OK To Adjust Rates, No OK For Rider UBA

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Two Integrys Energy Group Inc.

units received Illinois Commerce Commission approval to adjust their retail natural gas delivery rates, effective Feb. 14. The Chicago-based natural gas and electric utility operator said Peoples Gas Light and Coke Co. will boost its revenue by $71.2 million, while North Shore Gas will reduce its revenue by $213,000. The Commission rejected Rider UBA, which would permit the recovery of actual natural gas expenses, a portion of bad debt costs.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys Energy Gets OK To Adjust Rates, No OK For Rider UBA

Headlines.Headline: Illinois Commission OKs Integrys Natural Gas Rate Increase

PARAGRAPH.#text: CHICAGO (AP)--Action taken Tuesday by the Illinois Commerce Commission will mean customers of Peoples Gas & Light will be hit with a 4% to 5% rate increase that critics say will penalize consumers who conserve energy.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Illinois Commission OKs Integrys Natural Gas Rate Increase

Headlines.Author: Adam O. Manzor
Headlines.Headline: Integrys: Weston 3 Pwr Plant Returns To Service

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Integrys Energy Group Inc.

said a 321-megawatt electric power plant owned by its Wisconsin Public Service Corp. subsidiary returned to service after a three-month outage caused by a lightning strike on Oct. 6. The Chicago energy holding company said the Public Service Commission of Wisconsin approved the recovery of the cost of the Weston 3 replacement power, and operations and maintenance costs incurred to return the plant to service.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys: Weston 3 Pwr Plant Returns To Service

Headlines.Headline: Dividends Set Record in 2007

PARAGRAPH.#text: Companies in the S&P 500 paid a record $27.73 a share in dividends in 2007, and Standard & Poor's expects that amount to rise 9.3% in 2008.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Dividends Set Record in 2007
Headlines.Provider: The Wall Street Journal Interactive Edition

Headlines.Author: Kathy Shwiff
Headlines.Headline: S&P 500 Cos Paid Record Payouts Of $27.73/Shr In '07

#text: Companies in the S&P 500 Index paid a record $27.73 a share in dividends in 2007, and Standard & Poor's expects that amount to increase 9.3% in 2008. S&P, a unit of McGraw-Hill Cos.

, said the 11.5% increase in the combined per-share dividend from 2006 to 2007 resulted in a total of $246.6 billion in dividend payments. The combined dividend in 2008 is expected to reach $30.30 a share.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: S&P 500 Cos Paid Record Payouts Of $27.73/Shr In '07

Headlines.Author: Shirleen Dorman
Headlines.Headline: Integris Energy Unit Gets New Electric Rate In Michigan

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Wisconsin Public Service Corp., a subsidiary of Integrys Energy Group Inc.

, received approval to raise electric rates for about 9,000 retail customers in Menominee County, Mich. The increase, approved by the Michigan Public Service Commission, is effective Dec. 5. The Chicago holding company said the increase would add about $4.77 to the monthly bill of a typical residential customer using 600 kilowatt-hours.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integris Energy Unit Gets New Electric Rate In Michigan

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys Energy Raised To Outperform From Neutral By Baird

Headlines.Headline: Integrys Energy Group 3Q EPS 56c Vs EPS 91c

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Integrys Energy Group Inc.'s

third-quarter earnings increased to $43.9 million from $40.2 million a year earlier. On a per-share basis, the company's earnings fell to 56 cents from 91 cents because the company issued about 31.9 million shares of common stock in February. Income from continuing operations fell to $11.6 million, or 14 cents a share, from $28 million, or 63 cents a share, a year earlier.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys Energy Group 3Q EPS 56c Vs EPS 91c

Headlines.Author: James DeWeese
Headlines.Headline: Integrys Sees Weston 3 Plant Offline To Late 07-Early 08

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Integrys Energy Group Inc.'s

Wisconsin Public Service Corp. expects its Weston 3 power plant to remain out service until late 2007 or early 2008 as a result of an Oct. 6 lightning strike. Integrys, based in Chicago, said it doesn't believe that the incident will have a material impact on net income. Wisconsin Public Service Corp., based in Green Bay, Wis., said Wednesday that it expects replacement power costs to be at least $26 million.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys Sees Weston 3 Plant Offline To Late 07-Early 08

Headlines.Author: Adam Edelman
Headlines.Headline: Integrys Unit Seeks Cost Deferral Related To Lightning Strike

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Integrys Energy Group Inc.'s

Wisconsin Public Service Corp. unit said it will seek a deferral of the Wisconsin retail portion of the costs associated with one of its power plants that was struck by lightning on Oct. 6. Due to the strike, Wisconsin Public Service's Weston 3 power plant is expected to be out of service "beyond November." If the company receives a favorably regulatory outcome, it expects there will be no material impact on net income.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Integrys Unit Seeks Cost Deferral Related To Lightning Strike

Headlines.Author: Steve Gelsi
Headlines.Headline: El Paso Corp. paying $875 million for Integrys Energy reserves
Headlines.BodyHeadline: El Paso Corp. paying $875 million for Integrys Energy reserves

PARAGRAPH.#text: NEW YORK (MarketWatch) -- El Paso Corp. on Friday said it would pay $875 million in cash to buy reserves from Integrys Energy Group, with plans to finance the deal by the sale of assets in southern Texas and the Gulf of Mexico.

Headlines.Author: Jennifer Hodson
Headlines.Headline: Wisconsin Public Seeks To Recover Electric Reliability Costs

#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Integrys Energy Group Inc.'s

Wisconsin Public Service Corp. filed a request with the Public Service Commission of Wisconsin to recover deferred and expected charges from Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator Inc. The request, if approved, would result in a rate increase of 3.64%, or about $2.03 monthly for the typical residential electric customer using 630 kilowatthours of electricity, the company said.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Wisconsin Public Seeks To Recover Electric Reliability Costs
